1
00:00:09,531 --> 00:00:11,557
l love you.

2
00:00:14,404 --> 00:00:16,735
l love you.

3
00:00:18,341 --> 00:00:20,105
These two simple words...

4
00:00:20,843 --> 00:00:25,041
Who knows who were
the first to use them?

5
00:00:25,481 --> 00:00:26,915
Whom did he say them to?

6
00:00:28,452 --> 00:00:31,513
Whenever these words of love...

7
00:00:31,823 --> 00:00:34,348
... were uttered by anyone...

8
00:00:34,726 --> 00:00:39,857
The beautiful, innocent were
attracted like crazy magnets.

9
00:01:31,622 --> 00:01:34,751
Work fast or you'll
never complete in time!

10
00:01:35,459 --> 00:01:38,293
- The stage isn't ready as yet!
- lt will be.

11
00:01:38,764 --> 00:01:43,531
We'll have flowers there
and chandeliers in the center.

12
00:01:45,905 --> 00:01:48,238
Don't ruin the flowers.
What are you doing?

13
00:01:53,580 --> 00:01:56,106
You take the flowers
and give this to me.

14
00:02:01,089 --> 00:02:03,785
Brother is coming today.
Has somebody gone to the station?

15
00:02:04,092 --> 00:02:05,287
l've sent Anand.

16
00:02:12,201 --> 00:02:13,794
Guess who this is.

17
00:02:15,538 --> 00:02:20,306
One who can't be seen
in the daylight.

18
00:02:20,510 --> 00:02:23,344
My moon like daughter.

19
00:02:23,547 --> 00:02:25,641
The Chandni (moonlight)!

20
00:02:26,584 --> 00:02:28,643
Why did you have to guess so easily?

21
00:02:31,423 --> 00:02:36,190
Till the daughter is at home,
she is recognized.

22
00:02:37,663 --> 00:02:40,929
But when she gets married
and belongs to somebody else..

23
00:02:41,166 --> 00:02:44,330
Every relation ends.

24
00:02:45,872 --> 00:02:49,240
l've come for Neelu's wedding
but you're getting me married off!

25
00:02:49,577 --> 00:02:53,604
- l'm not getting married...
- After putting the frills...

26
00:02:56,784 --> 00:03:01,484
- How are you aunt?
- l am fine.

27
00:03:01,723 --> 00:03:04,191
But why are you so impatient?

28
00:03:04,593 --> 00:03:06,755
Why have got applied this paste?

29
00:03:07,263 --> 00:03:09,356
Should we get you also married?

30
00:03:09,599 --> 00:03:10,896
My foot will get married!

31
00:03:11,167 --> 00:03:13,965
- How are you dear?
- Very well.

32
00:03:14,270 --> 00:03:17,968
- Where is Neelu?
- Upstairs in her room.

33
00:03:26,284 --> 00:03:27,774
Couldn't you come earlier?

34
00:03:28,152 --> 00:03:29,983
There was so much work at home.

35
00:03:30,255 --> 00:03:33,521
- He should get leave.
- Some excuse always.

36
00:03:36,462 --> 00:03:39,829
- You've come like a guest.
- Let go!

37
00:03:40,065 --> 00:03:42,431
- Just 2 days before the wedding!
- l'll answer when you leave me.

38
00:03:43,535 --> 00:03:45,936
You're hugging the dust and
grime of the journey and my clothes!

39
00:03:46,172 --> 00:03:49,734
Does the moonlight ever
get dirty because of dust?

40
00:03:55,983 --> 00:03:58,714
Good God! What was that blast?

41
00:03:59,021 --> 00:04:04,049
- That's his style of coming home.
- Who is it who comes like a bomb?

42
00:04:04,294 --> 00:04:06,488
He's Anand's best friend, Rohit.

43
00:04:08,398 --> 00:04:10,457
Who has put rags
in place of canopy?

44
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:12,658
- That was me sir.
- You?

45
00:04:12,835 --> 00:04:16,567
This darned and sheet put up for
Rohit Gupta's sister's wedding!

46
00:04:16,774 --> 00:04:19,538
Sir, now you won't
see them anywhere.

47
00:04:19,810 --> 00:04:22,335
Remove them fast! Quick!

48
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:25,013
Have the flowers arrived?

49
00:04:37,129 --> 00:04:41,623
Check if my bags have come up.
And give me a dress to wear.

50
00:04:42,102 --> 00:04:44,831
We didn't meet for a year and
you've learnt yours and mine!

51
00:04:45,105 --> 00:04:46,834
All my clothes are yours.

52
00:04:50,510 --> 00:04:53,308
- Where is Chandni?
- Must be loafing somewhere.

53
00:05:31,089 --> 00:05:32,681
l was feeling cold.
Want to warm up my hands.

54
00:05:33,024 --> 00:05:35,357
Warming up your eyes or your hands?

55
00:05:35,995 --> 00:05:37,792
Come on. Go away.

56
00:10:43,304 --> 00:10:44,669
Do you know why it turned dark?

57
00:10:46,107 --> 00:10:50,374
So that it would only be
bright enough for me to see you.

58
00:10:50,846 --> 00:10:53,474
And you see only me.

59
00:10:58,087 --> 00:11:00,385
When the Maker must have made you..

60
00:11:00,656 --> 00:11:05,151
Even he must have been
swayed at least once.

61
00:11:06,930 --> 00:11:09,957
Maybe you don't know
how beautiful you are.

62
00:11:11,068 --> 00:11:16,439
So beautiful that the word
beautiful falls short.

63
00:11:17,108 --> 00:11:20,043
People have a tendency
to beat around the bush.

64
00:11:20,311 --> 00:11:22,610
But l speak the truth
and to the point.

65
00:11:23,048 --> 00:11:28,884
l love you as much as nobody
must have ever loved another!

66
00:11:29,288 --> 00:11:31,917
By now maybe you
too love me that much.

67
00:11:32,191 --> 00:11:33,989
Yes or no?

68
00:11:42,336 --> 00:11:43,769
Let me tell you another thing.

69
00:11:44,105 --> 00:11:48,941
We Delhites can rule the
country as well as the heart!

70
00:11:49,278 --> 00:11:52,304
We will win the heart!

71
00:12:06,230 --> 00:12:08,960
Nobody ever spoke to me
like this in Shahjahanpur.

72
00:12:09,533 --> 00:12:12,559
l was only my mother's daughter.

73
00:12:13,070 --> 00:12:16,062
My heart would beat there too.

74
00:12:16,607 --> 00:12:20,908
But in Delhi l can hear
my heart beat!

75
00:12:40,033 --> 00:12:42,661
l came from the village.

76
00:12:43,338 --> 00:12:48,366
When the time came to leave,
l started howling.

77
00:12:48,844 --> 00:12:52,610
l kept crying and held my
grandmother and said..

78
00:12:52,848 --> 00:12:55,783
l know nothing.

79
00:12:56,151 --> 00:12:59,178
What will happen? l know nothing!

80
00:13:01,925 --> 00:13:05,827
Come dear. You too
listen to this story.

81
00:13:06,096 --> 00:13:10,796
No teacher can teach you this.

82
00:13:11,102 --> 00:13:13,002
Come and sit with brother.

83
00:13:20,145 --> 00:13:23,080
Aunt you were telling us
about your honeymoon.

84
00:13:23,382 --> 00:13:26,681
ln our days, we had
a room of cow dung.

85
00:13:27,053 --> 00:13:30,512
l fell asleep waiting.

86
00:13:30,924 --> 00:13:33,485
Only then did your uncle come in.

87
00:13:33,861 --> 00:13:38,663
Now only he and l were in the room.

88
00:13:44,239 --> 00:13:47,539
Seeing me asleep,
he pinched me hard!

89
00:13:49,110 --> 00:13:53,241
What's wrong with you?
l was pinched 55 years ago.

90
00:13:53,516 --> 00:13:55,177
And you're feeling the hurt today?

91
00:13:55,651 --> 00:13:57,778
Nothing aunt.

92
00:13:58,421 --> 00:14:00,413
The romance has just begun.

93
00:14:02,592 --> 00:14:08,088
Then slowly your uncle
caught my hand.

94
00:14:08,633 --> 00:14:11,227
- Let go of me!
- That's just what l said.

95
00:14:11,536 --> 00:14:15,404
- Then what happened?
- What would happen?

96
00:14:15,707 --> 00:14:19,439
- Then he lifted me up.
- Then? Answer..

97
00:14:19,745 --> 00:14:21,940
l know you are very impatient.

98
00:14:22,215 --> 00:14:25,275
But nothing happened.

99
00:14:25,752 --> 00:14:30,212
He turned that way and slept off
and l turned the other!

100
00:14:30,690 --> 00:14:34,684
Does that mean that...
nothing happened?

101
00:14:35,029 --> 00:14:38,260
For 6 years we did nothing.

102
00:14:38,532 --> 00:14:45,233
The deed was done when
l turned 16 and he was 18.

103
00:14:45,707 --> 00:14:47,698
These days everything is hurried.

104
00:14:48,076 --> 00:14:49,805
Everything is instant.

105
00:14:54,617 --> 00:14:56,608
What do you say?

106
00:14:56,986 --> 00:14:59,147
lncidentally everything is instant.

107
00:14:59,555 --> 00:15:02,389
But when an accident takes place...

108
00:15:02,825 --> 00:15:07,820
We say, seasons keep changing
but spring has just arrived.

109
00:15:08,132 --> 00:15:09,498
Yes or no?

110
00:15:13,004 --> 00:15:15,838
You've got the right note.

111
00:15:16,141 --> 00:15:17,973
Hopefully the tune will be good.

112
00:15:27,287 --> 00:15:29,346
Yes or no?

113
00:15:32,827 --> 00:15:34,350
Come on answer, yes or no?

114
00:15:34,996 --> 00:15:38,022
- Will you serve or just ask?
- Serving!

115
00:16:03,994 --> 00:16:08,261
Henna is being applied to my palms
but the color is on your cheeks?

116
00:16:08,732 --> 00:16:11,395
This color is like a rainbow.

117
00:16:11,736 --> 00:16:15,638
lt is seen but can't be caught.

118
00:16:16,109 --> 00:16:22,571
lf the bride to be places her
hennaed hand in a spinster's hands...

119
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:25,250
She'll get engaged
and married right away.

120
00:16:25,619 --> 00:16:27,985
But if a boy holds a girl's hand...?

121
00:16:28,288 --> 00:16:31,621
Then they fall in love. lsn't it?

122
00:18:23,917 --> 00:18:26,181
Why are you pouncing on them?

123
00:18:26,519 --> 00:18:28,920
The bride has gone but the
photographs aren't running away.

124
00:18:29,189 --> 00:18:33,991
Your wife is running away. She
insists on leaving by evening.

125
00:18:35,496 --> 00:18:39,399
Are you all leaving today?

126
00:18:39,701 --> 00:18:43,637
- lt's a matter of my job.
- Dad, wedding photographs.

127
00:18:43,872 --> 00:18:47,673
Chandni has leave. Neelu has
gone to her husband's house.

128
00:18:48,111 --> 00:18:51,512
lf she stayed back,
she'd share our loneliness.

129
00:18:52,382 --> 00:18:56,547
Has the goddess of wealth and
a daughter ever stayed in one place?

130
00:18:56,787 --> 00:18:58,379
She may stay if she feels like it.

131
00:18:58,722 --> 00:19:02,056
At least now come and help me pack.

132
00:19:02,360 --> 00:19:05,352
Yelling won't help pack. Here.

133
00:19:22,181 --> 00:19:24,047
Will you stay?

134
00:19:27,587 --> 00:19:30,318
- Yes aunt.
- Are you happy?

135
00:19:30,590 --> 00:19:32,923
Yes l'm very happy.

136
00:19:34,896 --> 00:19:39,129
You're my favorite. That's why
l'm keeping you back to love you more.

137
00:19:39,467 --> 00:19:42,232
Does she only know how to
take love or even give?

138
00:19:42,504 --> 00:19:45,736
lf there's a tiny bit
of place in her heart...

139
00:19:46,009 --> 00:19:47,806
l'll send in an application.

140
00:19:48,077 --> 00:19:51,640
When you fool around, you don't
care if there are grown ups around!

141
00:19:51,882 --> 00:19:53,371
Coming.

142
00:19:55,286 --> 00:19:58,221
Don't the people in
Delhi have any shame?

143
00:19:58,456 --> 00:20:03,918
lf l feel shame, l'll be waving
a flag atop Qutub Minar all my life!

144
00:20:04,262 --> 00:20:08,198
Only if l be shameless
will l climb astride the horse.

145
00:20:08,467 --> 00:20:11,664
- Yes or no?
- You clicked even the horse.

146
00:20:11,971 --> 00:20:13,996
But kept flashing lights at me!

147
00:20:14,339 --> 00:20:16,808
- There's no picture of me!
- First answer yes or no.

148
00:20:17,176 --> 00:20:21,375
- lf l say no?
- l won't come on a horse.

149
00:20:21,715 --> 00:20:23,979
Will you sit on a donkey then?

150
00:20:24,385 --> 00:20:26,547
l will...

151
00:20:42,171 --> 00:20:45,698
No! l'm frightened!

152
00:20:47,444 --> 00:20:49,878
l'm with you!

153
00:20:52,215 --> 00:20:57,119
- l will die! - l won't
let you die before you answer!

154
00:20:57,522 --> 00:21:01,755
- l will fall off!
- Then come closer.

155
00:21:03,261 --> 00:21:06,231
- l am scared.
- Then hold me tight!

156
00:21:11,304 --> 00:21:12,964
Yes or no?

157
00:21:14,374 --> 00:21:16,968
- Yes or no?
- Yes!

158
00:21:17,410 --> 00:21:19,311
- Louder, l can't hear.
- Yes! Yes!

159
00:27:09,269 --> 00:27:11,737
When will you come again?

160
00:27:12,039 --> 00:27:16,066
-When you call me.
- Give me your address. l'll write.

161
00:27:16,276 --> 00:27:20,714
- lf mother finds out...
- l'll write at some friend's address.

162
00:27:26,822 --> 00:27:31,191
Letter! A letter from your lover!

163
00:27:33,863 --> 00:27:36,332
Give it to me! Don't trouble me!

164
00:27:37,834 --> 00:27:39,631
First l'll read it.

165
00:27:39,903 --> 00:27:41,804
lt came to my address.
l have a right to read it.

166
00:27:42,105 --> 00:27:48,045
According to our deal, l will
read it and you will hear.

167
00:27:51,449 --> 00:27:55,477
- Just hold this.
- Cheat!

168
00:27:57,322 --> 00:27:59,654
l'll show you when
the next letter comes!

169
00:28:12,172 --> 00:28:16,837
Should l call you the
breeze or the desire of time?

170
00:28:17,344 --> 00:28:20,837
The beat of my heart or
the fragrance of my breath?

171
00:28:21,650 --> 00:28:24,779
Flowers bloom when l think of you.

172
00:28:25,154 --> 00:28:30,592
When dawn breaks it feels as if
you are tossing your hair in dew.

173
00:28:31,327 --> 00:28:34,058
And l'm kissing your eyes.

174
00:28:34,997 --> 00:28:38,764
The golden afternoon feels as if
the moonlight has come to earth.

175
00:28:39,136 --> 00:28:44,369
The setting sun adorns you
with orange blossoms.

176
00:28:44,708 --> 00:28:47,838
And your fragrance reaches me.

177
00:28:50,048 --> 00:28:53,449
When night spreads
her cloak of darkness...

178
00:28:53,686 --> 00:28:56,154
l swear l miss you a lot!

179
00:28:58,757 --> 00:29:03,491
The full moon stops in its'
orbit to admire your beauty.

180
00:29:05,399 --> 00:29:09,529
l shut my eyes and
Chandni enters my heart.

181
00:29:10,337 --> 00:29:12,863
Yours and only yours.

182
00:29:23,885 --> 00:29:27,287
What do l write?
Time has come to a standstill.

183
00:29:28,023 --> 00:29:33,724
Time, night, breeze, fragrance,
everything holds its' breath and...

184
00:29:33,930 --> 00:29:35,626
Waits for me to write something.

185
00:29:35,866 --> 00:29:38,357
But how can the feelings
of the heart form words?

186
00:29:38,669 --> 00:29:42,298
All your favorite things are present.

187
00:29:42,606 --> 00:29:47,738
Jasmine flowers, a smiling flame
and your Chandni.

188
00:29:49,681 --> 00:29:51,148
l wish you were here.

189
00:29:51,783 --> 00:29:54,013
But how can you be here?

190
00:29:55,054 --> 00:29:56,783
But you are here.

191
00:29:58,190 --> 00:30:01,592
ln my heart and its' beats.

192
00:30:03,095 --> 00:30:06,863
Soon our hearts will beat like one.

193
00:30:07,300 --> 00:30:11,930
My parents will return tomorrow.
l'll talk to them about our wedding.

194
00:30:12,306 --> 00:30:15,935
You want to marry a girl
you saw in that crowd?

195
00:30:16,210 --> 00:30:18,179
A girl who is not of our standing,
who is not from our community!

196
00:30:18,580 --> 00:30:22,072
You want to make her the
daughter-in-law of our family?

197
00:30:22,317 --> 00:30:23,784
What are you talking about?

198
00:30:24,087 --> 00:30:26,988
l'm not the first man to do this.

199
00:30:27,290 --> 00:30:31,420
When we buy furniture we first
check if it matches in our house.

200
00:30:33,696 --> 00:30:37,326
The girl l love is
furniture for you?

201
00:30:37,734 --> 00:30:42,069
This word, love has been used
so often that it has lost meaning!

202
00:30:42,273 --> 00:30:45,471
Why do you forget that she
will get married and come here?

203
00:30:45,710 --> 00:30:48,645
- We'll have to adjust with her!
- Understand one thing mother.

204
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:50,542
l'm not marrying her for you.

205
00:30:50,782 --> 00:30:54,275
Neither do l believe in caste,
community and society norms.

206
00:30:54,487 --> 00:30:56,682
l haven't come to ask you
nor to take your permission.

207
00:30:56,889 --> 00:31:00,484
But only to inform you that
l am marrying her.

208
00:31:00,726 --> 00:31:03,491
You only have to decide whether
you will bless us or not!

209
00:31:06,533 --> 00:31:11,028
Stop him. lf she comes to
this house as a bride...

210
00:31:11,272 --> 00:31:13,068
What face will l have in society?

211
00:31:13,373 --> 00:31:15,842
Which society are you talking about?

212
00:31:16,177 --> 00:31:19,112
Where your bank balance
decides your reputation?

213
00:31:19,448 --> 00:31:21,439
That girl won't come to our house!

214
00:31:21,683 --> 00:31:23,652
You can't darn silk with rags!

215
00:31:23,886 --> 00:31:27,151
That was done the day l came
to this house as a son-in-law.

216
00:31:27,490 --> 00:31:29,516
And how will you stop him?

217
00:31:29,860 --> 00:31:32,328
He's a man of today, your only son.

218
00:31:32,562 --> 00:31:35,861
Someday he'll leave everything
and walk off. Think about it.

219
00:31:37,101 --> 00:31:41,128
Try to understand, weddings
are between people of same standing.

220
00:31:41,372 --> 00:31:42,738
We have to live in this society.

221
00:31:42,941 --> 00:31:47,344
The society that has accepted me
will accept her tomorrow.

222
00:31:47,746 --> 00:31:51,877
Actually he knows he is our only son.

223
00:31:52,251 --> 00:31:55,415
We can't go against his wishes.

224
00:31:56,855 --> 00:31:58,551
He's exploiting this fact.

225
00:31:59,459 --> 00:32:04,659
- Talk to Shivsagar..
- What are you...?

226
00:32:04,932 --> 00:32:06,991
But remember one thing.

227
00:32:07,301 --> 00:32:11,032
The wedding should be
worthy of our position.

228
00:36:26,256 --> 00:36:29,191
They treated us very well!
This boy has dishonored us!

229
00:36:29,493 --> 00:36:32,395
The daughter-in-law is the honor
and shame of the family, the house.

230
00:36:32,664 --> 00:36:35,064
She remains behind curtains
and maintains her distance.

231
00:36:35,500 --> 00:36:40,063
With her around we'll have a ball.

232
00:36:40,406 --> 00:36:45,400
We'll see dances everyday.
The neighbors too won't get bored.

233
00:36:45,745 --> 00:36:48,235
l still say break the relation.
lt's not too late!

234
00:36:49,783 --> 00:36:55,312
She didn't want to dance or sing.
Your darling son forced her into it.

235
00:36:55,689 --> 00:37:00,559
ln saving your reputation,
you may end up losing your son!

236
00:37:00,928 --> 00:37:05,592
They will come tomorrow.
Rearrange your facial expressions.

237
00:37:06,201 --> 00:37:07,634
- What did he say?
- Nothing.

238
00:37:17,312 --> 00:37:20,875
Congratulations!
Happiness and joy!

239
00:37:21,085 --> 00:37:22,642
Take our picture.

240
00:37:26,824 --> 00:37:28,883
Mother you are forgetting
the bride-to-be.

241
00:37:37,836 --> 00:37:42,297
- Live long son. - Today is also
the girl's day. Bless her also.

242
00:37:42,708 --> 00:37:44,972
Always be happy.

243
00:37:56,957 --> 00:38:01,326
Our love and blessings are in
this ring. Be happy son.

244
00:38:07,436 --> 00:38:11,167
The beauty of the ornament lies
in the wearer and love has no value.

245
00:38:12,107 --> 00:38:14,541
The beauty also lies with
the person putting it on.

246
00:38:15,511 --> 00:38:17,810
- Here put it on her finger.
- Yes.

247
00:38:25,489 --> 00:38:27,683
Won't you give her any gift?

248
00:38:28,125 --> 00:38:31,254
How can l forget my
future sister-in-law?

249
00:38:31,796 --> 00:38:36,791
l thought she's very fond of dancing
so what could be better than this?

250
00:38:39,304 --> 00:38:41,067
l am fond of dancing but..

251
00:38:43,142 --> 00:38:46,873
